But it happens every day. Intentional, unintentional, murders, suicide, it happens every day and there is so much evidence that if guns were not so readily available, if we had universal background checks, if we could just put some time out between the person who is upset because he got fired, or the domestic abuse, or whatever other motivation may be working on someone who does this, then maybe we could prevent this kind of carnage.
